76561198002189495,Recommended,329610,15631319,"Posted: 30 April, 2015",all,rovaira2,"This is a nice game. It's a retro style Baseball game with an arcade feel to it. The graphics are decent; not over the top, and not bad either. It's good to see an MLB game on the PC.Positives:A Baseball game back on the PCWorks with a Logitech Dual Action Controller, however some of the controls don't match up; hit is button 1, bunt button 2, steal button 3 (and direction).  All of those controls are easy to use though. :)Pitching and hitting are funSeason mode with statsChoice of 162 games in a season, 82, or 51. (Yes season mode appears to work now so far. the relief pitcher bug is now fixed. :)MLB rostersSounds of the crowd are pretty good, they cheer when they should; sounds cool when someone hits a homerun as wellGames can be played in a reasonable amount of time. I lost 6-2 in my first season game and it lasted around 45 minutes. It took me 1-2 exhibition games to get used to the controls, but they are pretty good.Minus:Fielding is a bit tough at first, but you can set it on assist which means the fielders do the fielding and you do the throwing if needed.Graphics could be betterNo Myplayer, and no trades.Mouse control in the menus (or at all) isn't supported; have to use keyboard or gamepad.There are a few bugs I ran into like a pitcher fielding the ball in the 12th on the mound, and he couldn't throw or move. This only happened once so far though.Overall:Pick up this game if you want a decent MLB game, and you want to support PC sports games."
,Not Recommended,329610,18685320,"Posted: 25 October, 2015",all,Orge Lambart,"This is about as bare bones as you can get for a sports game,  Very limited options, no trades during the season, no free agency, no multiple seasons...  it's generally lacking in many areas which sports games have become known for in recent years.The good -  it has the official MLB license, which means real teams and players.  It's simplistic and very casual, you can just pick up and play, other than getting timing down for hitting it's easy to play.  If you are an older gamer you'll appriciate the throw back to old sports games.The bad  -  The game just isn't anywhere near the standard sports games have been held too far years.  Lack of options, lack of customization, lack of multiple seasons.  While these things were common place back in the the early 2000's when games were limited, those limitations don't exist anymore.  The graphics are kind of meh, that normally doesn't matter in sports games but the player animations are rough, they glide rather than run.  Also it seems to have quite a few issues with fielding on line drives...Generally speaking, Super Mega Baseball is a far superior product, which is only held back by it's lack of a MLB license.  I'd only recommend this game if you're a massive hardcore fan of throwback games.  Even then it's a tough recommendation because the game just isn't very fun to play.."
